reviews.review_text:
great greatest story alabama is solid playing with jerr everywhere but as a 95 goes first couple of songs sound tight 

cant wait for the
Saint Of Circumstance 


any dead is a 5 star

This was sad We were in fourth row center reserved seats.

When pasty Jerry took the stage the woman next to me broke into tears and there was stunned silence.

She whispered to me "This is not good"

It was the last time I saw the man play.

R.I.P  Big bro

June's 70th Birthday My mom went to the June 2nd and June 3rd shows with me. It was her 70th birthday on the 3rd. When the Gyuto monks chanted before space her third eye popped open!I'll never forget those shows and neither will she! I was so glad she got to see the boys before Jerry was gone. Big Fun!

It's time a myth was laid to rest. If you think ANY Dead is 5 stars, then this is a 5-star show. I, on the other hand, liked the Dead because sometimes they actually played good music.

If this is the highest-rated show of the year (before I came along), it's a sad commentary on either the year or the taste of Deadheads.

Tight for 95 Some quite energetic playing here for late in the GDs life. Two nights later was my last show. One of the worst and saddest GD shows of my 50 year GD career. Two months later Jerry would be dead.
